{{Collapse|num=1|final=|initial=<center><big>Have you ever held the glass bottle regarded as infinite hope late at night, quietly watching the star river inside flow slowly?</big></center>|body={{Collapse|num=2|final=|initial=<center><big>Have you ever realized that the bottle holds more than a sealed universe; those eyes woven from starlight are gazing back at you silently through the glass?</big></center>|body={{Collapse|num=3|final=|initial=<center><big>The star rivers entrusted with all hopes have long silently recorded the sufferings hidden in every heart.</big></center>|body={{Collapse|num=4|final=|initial=<center><big>The so-called starry sky shall not only lead you to salvation,<br>but also drag you down into an abyss from which there is no return.</big></center>|body={{Collapse|num=5|final=|initial=<center><big><big>Let us trace back to the origin.</big></big></center>|body=

Amid the endless darkness of the Backrooms, Bottled Starlight is a being born from despair yet bearing hope, a spiritual vessel holding boundless optimism. Much like an utterly pure sponge, it silently absorbs the darkness within every soul that touches it, returning healing and comfort in exchange—yet day after day, it gradually becomes tainted itself.

The Major Explorer Group and Star Worshippers saw this value, and with full devotion they launched the Star Curtain Project, striving to turn this miracle into hope for all.

The days after the Star Curtain Project launched were once deemed the warmest and most momentous era across the Backrooms. Shared Starlight Warehouses were erected one after another; the Starlight Recipes were refined, printed and distributed time and again. Wanderers learned safe methods to collect and blend Bottled Starlight, no longer scrambling for it blindly, nor slaying one another for possessing such a coveted treasure. People believed that so long as the project pressed forward, suffering in the Backrooms would lessen, and loneliness would fade away.

All souls fell into a beautiful dream beneath the starlight, fully convinced they had found the ultimate solution to resist the horrors of the Backrooms.

But Bottled Starlight is far more than just an object, a resource. It is a silent observer, recording the struggles, greed, fear and breakdown of every soul. If you stare into the starry sky long enough, the sky will memorize your face. If countless pairs of despairing eyes fixate upon the starry sky together, the sky will be completely blackened, then turn around and mercilessly send all accumulated agony back to every soul within the Backrooms.

When the Star Curtain Project brought starlight into mass circulation, when countless tormented consciousnesses tainted the same stretch of star river day in and day out—the fear of one wanderer, the anxiety of ten, the despair of a hundred, the mental collapse of a thousand… Even the purest starlight could not bear such an overwhelming weight.

The sponge that seemed capable of containing everything finally released all the filth it had soaked up, pouring it back upon humanity.

<center>
<div style="margin-top: 50px; display: inline-block; box-shadow: 0 0 10px grey, 0 0 20px white, 0 0 30px royalblue, 0 0 40px lightblue, 0 0 50px royalblue;">[[File:混沌蓝色.jpeg|500px|link=]]</div>
<div style="margin-top: 70px; margin-bottom: 50px;">
<div style="display: inline-block; width: 550px; font-size: 13px;"><code>𝚏𝚒𝚐 1.0:</code><span style="margin-left: 1rem;"></span>Chaotic, distorted, disordered.</div>
</div>
</center>

The collapse of the Star Curtain Project unfolded far faster than its construction.

All catastrophes begin with trivial anomalies, and the Star Curtain Project’s fall was no exception. One bottle of starlight appeared slightly warped; a wisp of star radiance dimmed faintly; a dish prepared from the starlight recipes carried a subtle bitter aftertaste. No one paid mind to these changes. All dismissed them as natural wear, individual variance, or trivial blips amid the boundless chaos of the Backrooms.

As time wore on, however, more and more batches of starlight began exhibiting abnormal behavior. Inside the Shared Starlight Warehouses, massive quantities of Bottled Starlight turned scarlet and chaotic. The once brilliant, clear star rivers twisted and warped, losing their enchanting glow and instead oozing eerie icy crimson mist that eroded the heart.

The Backrooms environment itself began to be disturbed by the corrupted starlight. Zones hosting Shared Starlight Warehouses saw a sharp drop in level spatial stability; fleeting glimpses of other levels would surface on the walls, while floors often softened to a water-like texture.

<center>
<div style="margin-top: 50px; display: inline-block; box-shadow: 0 0 10px grey, 0 0 20px white, 0 0 30px royalblue, 0 0 40px lightblue, 0 0 50px royalblue;">[[File:混沌蓝色background.jpeg|500px|link=]]</div>
<div style="margin-top: 70px; margin-bottom: 50px;">
<div style="display: inline-block; width: 550px; font-size: 13px;"><code>𝚏𝚒𝚐 2.0:</code><span style="margin-left: 1rem;"></span>Until the first incident of corruption broke out.</div>
</div>
</center>

Gradually, the Starlight Recipes transformed into catastrophe formulas. Dishes cooked strictly per the recipe instructions, once tainted with corrupted stardust, morphed from soul-healing remedies into poisons that doom all who consume them. Drinkers would instantly be flooded with the despairing memories of countless strangers, crushed by layers upon layers of overlapping terror and trapped in permanent insanity. The Shared Starlight Warehouses, once safe hubs and spiritual sanctuaries, became sources of contamination and flashpoints for mass hysteria. Every wanderer who entered or exited accelerated the spread of darkness.

The system once built to foster mutual aid had turned into the most efficient panic dissemination network; the recipes crafted to save lives had become the fastest method of destroying souls.

The Major Explorer Group attempted to seal off, quarantine and incinerate contaminated samples, only to discover corrupted starlight had gained the ability to self-propagate. It could lie dormant within bottle glass, cling to consciousnesses, and seep into every corner of the Backrooms via wandering wanderers, silently spreading across level after level. The faith of the Star Worshippers crumbled entirely; those who had devoted themselves most fervently to guarding the starlight were the first to be consumed by the darkness they protected, turning into irrational fanatics roaming about to spread corrupted star radiance. The collaborative framework between the two Groups shattered in an instant, order vanished, and trust ceased to exist.

Meanwhile, the wanderers who had once shared starlight for survival now turned on one another with suspicion, attacking and fleeing. The entire Backrooms was engulfed in a massive panic ignited by starlight.

Mankind finally understood that the Star Curtain Project had been flawed from its very inception.

They only saw the immense value of Bottled Starlight, only sought ways to develop, exploit and share it—yet they never considered that the starry sky watched them right back. They treated starlight as a disposable resource at their beck and call, unaware it had been observing all along, steadily accumulating every trace of darkness within the Backrooms. They thought they were building hope, yet in truth they erected a colossal cage, gathering, compressing and fermenting all humanity’s suffering within it, ultimately birthing an irreversible disaster.

When the final Shared Starlight Warehouse was shut down, the last copy of the Starlight Recipes burned, and the last vial of pure Bottled Starlight vanished into the dark, the Star Curtain Project was officially declared a total failure.

The Backrooms slipped back into a state colder and more terrifying than it had ever been before.

People no longer believed in sharing, no longer believed in hope, and dared not even glance at any speck of light. They knew those glimmers might hide countless staring eyes, the pain of innumerable souls, and a gaze capable of dragging a person down into the abyss.

The corrupted starlight shards remain scattered across every corner of the Backrooms, silently watching every passing wanderer within the dark.

